==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[Hindi]] चाँपो ''champo'', the [[imperative]] form of the verb [[चाँपना]] ''champna'', meaning “to press or knead” i.e., to [[massage]]. <!--what's the reference for this etymology? -->

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''shampoo'''

# A traditional [[Indian]] and [[Persian]] body [[massage]] given after pouring [[warm]] [[water]] over the body and rubbing it with [[extract]]s from [[herb]]s.
# A [[commercial]] [[liquid]] [[soap]] product for [[wash]]ing [[hair]] or other fibres/fibers, such as [[carpet]]s.
# An instance of washing the hair or other fibres with shampoo.
#: ''I’m going to give the carpet a '''shampoo'''.''
# {{italbrac|humorous slang}} [[Champagne]] {{italbrac|wine}}.

